ents":[{"title":"Chilli mayonnaise","content":["1 fresh chilli, trimmed and deseeded","80 g mayonnaise (see Tips)","2 tsp lime juice"]},{"title":"Mussel fritters","content":["500 g water","1000 g mussels, New Zealand green lipped, cleaned and debearded","2 spring onions\/shallots, cut into pieces (approx. 3 cm)","2 garlic cloves","2 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, plus 24 leaves for garnishig","100 g full cream milk","50 g plain flour","1 tsp baking powder","1 egg","½ tsp salt","2 pinches freshly ground black pepper","5 - 6 tbsp vegetable oil, plus extra for frying","30 g sweet potato, unpeeled and julienned (approx 5 cm long)","20 g fresh ginger (5 cm piece), julienned","1 fresh red chilli, trimmed, deseeded and julienned"]}],"id":"r131032","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-WKZ4aJBDKk0\/XZMv0_ck1iI\/AAAAAAAAaWo\/-lcnRjPI0psQtVZPXKH5lcdTmDIbqQpvgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_qUNUtlcBigRfePsZ.png","title":"Mussel fritters with chilli mayonnaise","publishedAt":"2017-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"42.9 g","fat":"56.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26.8 g","calories":"3284 kJ \/ 781.9 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, non-stick frying pan, plate, paper towel, refrigerator, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["The New Zealand green lipped mussel differs from other mussel species in that it has dark brown\/green shells with green lips around the edges, and only has one adductor muscle. It is also one of the largest mussel species.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook or Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for Mayonnaise recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}